272
00:19:10,699 --> 00:19:14,430
You're not ready to get married and
I think you should look at that and...

273
00:19:14,636 --> 00:19:15,796
Please?

274
00:19:19,374 --> 00:19:23,868
<i>I'm thinking maybe I should get
in touch with Hodgemeyer for this case.</i>

275
00:19:25,214 --> 00:19:26,806
Reservation for Hodgemeyer...

276
00:19:27,115 --> 00:19:28,241
...Mitchell...

277
00:19:28,450 --> 00:19:29,542
...Hodgemeyer.

278
00:19:30,385 --> 00:19:32,285
This guy will be a pain in the ass.

279
00:19:32,554 --> 00:19:35,216
- Try to figure out which bank it is.
- All right.

280
00:19:36,792 --> 00:19:40,523
We got one shot to break through this.
Tomorrow afternoon.

281
00:19:40,729 --> 00:19:42,788
That's about the size of it.

282
00:19:45,133 --> 00:19:46,794
Easy enough.

283
00:19:49,805 --> 00:19:52,831
<i>It's not without serious
reservation that I begin...</i>

284
00:19:53,041 --> 00:19:55,339
<i>... the seemingly impossible task...</i>

285
00:19:55,544 --> 00:19:58,308
<i>... of documenting my own methods.</i>

286
00:19:58,981 --> 00:20:00,346
<i>It always seemed that...</i>

287
00:20:00,549 --> 00:20:02,210
<i>... someone else should do it.</i>

288
00:20:02,484 --> 00:20:05,578
<i>Unfortunately, my faithful
legal representative...</i>

289
00:20:05,787 --> 00:20:08,722
<i>... has shown no interest whatsoever.</i>

290
00:20:08,991 --> 00:20:12,620
<i>And so I am forced
to take on the task myself...</i>

291
00:20:12,828 --> 00:20:14,295
<i>... with no intention...</i>

292
00:20:14,496 --> 00:20:19,195
<i>... of glorifying or aggrandizing
or immortalizing my own memory...</i>

293
00:20:19,401 --> 00:20:20,959
<i>... but rather in the hope...</i>

294
00:20:21,169 --> 00:20:23,194
<i>... that such a memoir might someday...</i>

295
00:20:23,405 --> 00:20:24,736
<i>... be useful to others.</i>

296
00:20:25,173 --> 00:20:27,073
<i>I begin my examination...</i>

297
00:20:27,342 --> 00:20:28,741
<i>... of the method.</i>

298
00:20:29,711 --> 00:20:32,202
<i>I always say my work
relies fundamentally...</i>

299
00:20:32,414 --> 00:20:34,473
<i>... on two basic principles:</i>

300
00:20:35,250 --> 00:20:38,219
<i>Objectivity and observation.</i>

301
00:20:38,420 --> 00:20:40,911
<i>Or the 2 Obs, as I call them.</i>

302
00:20:43,926 --> 00:20:47,157
<i>My work relies on my ability
to remain absolutely...</i>

303
00:20:47,362 --> 00:20:48,488
<i>... purely...</i>

304
00:20:48,697 --> 00:20:49,755
<i>... objective.</i>

305
00:20:50,265 --> 00:20:51,596
<i>Detached.</i>

306
00:20:54,536 --> 00:20:56,163
<i>I have mastered...</i>

307
00:20:56,371 --> 00:20:57,565
<i>... the fine art...</i>

308
00:20:57,773 --> 00:20:59,035
<i>... of detachment.</i>

309
00:20:59,374 --> 00:21:02,077
<i>And while it comes at some cost...</i>

310
00:21:02,077 --> 00:21:04,443
<i>... this supreme objectivity is what
makes me...</i>

311
00:21:05,180 --> 00:21:09,844
<i>... I dare say, the greatest observer
the world has ever known.</i>

312
00:21:36,478 --> 00:21:39,447
<i>Observing a subject,
particularly a client...</i>

313
00:21:39,648 --> 00:21:44,017
<i>... in his or her own element
is usually very telling.</i>

314
00:21:44,219 --> 00:21:48,519
<i>Behavior is always more revealing
than language...</i>

315
00:21:48,657 --> 00:21:50,648
<i>... if you know what to look for.</i>

316
00:21:53,662 --> 00:21:56,426
No rain. Would you believe it?

317
00:21:56,999 --> 00:21:58,830
What? You talking to me?

318
00:21:59,167 --> 00:22:03,433
