Are you sure it's okay?

746
00:53:10,467 --> 00:53:11,900
I'll just...

747
00:53:12,169 --> 00:53:13,136
...be here.

748
00:53:14,638 --> 00:53:17,232
Just yell if you need anything else.

749
00:53:53,110 --> 00:53:54,805
How's it going over there?

750
00:53:55,012 --> 00:53:56,809
Just another minute.

751
00:53:57,014 --> 00:53:58,845
I'm rechecking my math.

752
00:54:03,854 --> 00:54:05,981
You really ought to try...

753
00:54:06,189 --> 00:54:07,816
...to keep all your receipts...

754
00:54:08,025 --> 00:54:09,617
...for everything.

755
00:54:10,961 --> 00:54:12,792
I know. I never remember.

756
00:54:19,536 --> 00:54:21,163
Just put them in an envelope.

757
00:54:21,371 --> 00:54:24,636
That's the thing to do.
I try to keep all my receipts.

758
00:54:25,142 --> 00:54:27,372
It's just a matter of habit now.

759
00:54:30,380 --> 00:54:32,644
I can't thank you enough.

760
00:54:33,317 --> 00:54:35,376
You really helped me out there.

761
00:54:36,386 --> 00:54:37,546
That's...

762
00:54:37,888 --> 00:54:39,651
...really my pleasure.

763
00:54:43,327 --> 00:54:44,726
Okay, listen.

764
00:54:45,896 --> 00:54:47,386
Let me make you dinner.

765
00:54:51,001 --> 00:54:54,061
No, you don't have to do that.

766
00:54:54,938 --> 00:54:56,200
I insist.

767
00:54:56,406 --> 00:54:59,569
I'll hop in the shower real quick,
then make us some food.

768
00:55:02,245 --> 00:55:03,405
All right.

769
00:57:15,812 --> 00:57:16,938
"Retired."

770
00:57:17,147 --> 00:57:18,205
Jesus!

771
00:57:18,415 --> 00:57:19,575
Another 7-letter word.

772
00:57:19,783 --> 00:57:21,444
17 plus 50...

773
00:57:21,651 --> 00:57:23,050
...67 points.

774
00:57:25,722 --> 00:57:27,053
Retire.

775
00:57:30,827 --> 00:57:32,055
Retire.

776
00:57:34,164 --> 00:57:35,859
It's not quite that simple.

777
00:57:36,399 --> 00:57:38,833
Why is it not that simple, Steve?

778
00:57:39,503 --> 00:57:41,300
Whenever you say that...

779
00:57:41,505 --> 00:57:42,665
...it creeps me out.

780
00:57:43,740 --> 00:57:46,504
I told you, it's nothing weird.

781
00:57:47,677 --> 00:57:51,738
I mean, okay, yes. It's a little weird.
But it's nothing creepy...

782
00:57:53,517 --> 00:57:54,916
...exactly.

783
00:57:55,852 --> 00:57:57,717
What do you get out of this?

784
00:57:57,921 --> 00:58:01,322
What kind of a hold does this guy,
whoever he is...

785
00:58:01,525 --> 00:58:02,753
...have on you?

786
00:58:05,362 --> 00:58:06,852
He needs me.

787
00:58:12,269 --> 00:58:13,702
He needs you.

788
00:58:17,374 --> 00:58:18,864
Who needs who?

789
00:58:26,716 --> 00:58:28,047
I need you.

790
00:58:31,721 --> 00:58:34,121
It's time to get away from him, Steve.

791
00:58:49,806 --> 00:58:51,967
I'll do it tomorrow when I get there...

792
00:58:53,977 --> 00:58:55,035
...if...

793
00:58:55,245 --> 00:58:57,270
...you will marry me.

794
00:59:07,591 --> 00:59:08,819
Marry me.

795
00:59:16,333 --> 00:59:17,960
<i>Absolutely vital:</i>

796
00:59:18,168 --> 00:59:20,602
<i>The ability to blend in.</i>

797
00:59:21,171 --> 00:59:24,265
<i>To very discreetly assimilate.</i>

798
00:59:24,608 --> 00:59:26,473
<i>It's not usually very difficult.</i>

799
00:59:26,676 --> 00:59:29,076
<i>All you have to do is look around...</i>

800
00:59:29,279 --> 00:59:31,747
<i>... see how all the ordinary people
are behaving...</i>

801
00:59:31,948 --> 00:59:34,178
<i>... and try to behave like one of them.</i>

802
00:59:39,856 --> 00:59:42,017
You know, when I was in L. A...

803
00:59:42,459 --> 00:59:45,121
...it seemed like such a lonely town.

804
00:59:46,630 --> 00:59:50,999
Everybody's driving in their cars,
nobody talks to each other...

805
00:59:55,305 --> 00:59:58,297
I don't really know,
to tell you the truth...

806
00:59:58,875 --> 01:00:00,308
...about that.

807
01:00:02,045 --> 01:00:03,808
So where are you from?

808
01:00:04,047 --> 01:00:05,378
Originally?

809
01:00:07,717 --> 01:00:09,048
Minnesota.

810
01:00:10,487 --> 01:00:11,886
Minnesota.

811
01:00:13,890 --> 01:00:15,619
I've never been there.

812
01:00:15,825 --> 01:00:17,725
Do you go back there much?

813
01:00:24,334 --> 01:00:26,325
You still have family there?

814
01:00:32,075 --> 01:00:34,066
We're not really in touch.

815
01:00:37,013 --> 01:00:38,173
So...

816
01:00:39,082 --> 01:00:41,676
...what are you doing in L.A.?

817
01:00:45,021 --> 01:00:47,581
Oh, I was there twice.

818
01:00:50,760 --> 01:00:53,092
Once when I was little.

819
01:00:54,097 --> 01:00:56,531
I was there with my aunt and uncle.

820
01:00:57,033 --> 01:01:00,366
I was raised by my aunt and uncle.
They adopted me.

821
01:01:03,440 --> 01:01:06,432
Then last year I was there skydiving.

822
01:01:07,377 --> 01:01:08,776
Skydiving?

823
01:01:13,717 --> 01:01:15,184
Why do you do that?

824
01:01:16,052 --> 01:01:17,781
Because I love it.

825
01:01:19,122 --> 01:01:21,556
It's the most amazing
thing in the world.

826
01:01:22,759 --> 01:01:25,227
Aren't you afraid you'll die
or something?

827
01:01:28,064 --> 01:01:29,895
I know what you need.

828
01:01:37,741 --> 01:01:38,901
Try again.

829
01:01:40,010 --> 01:01:42,672
Take your time now.
Really set yourself.

830
01:01:43,747 --> 01:01:46,011
Remember to bend your elbows a little.

831
01:01:47,183 --> 01:01:48,480
A little less.

832
01:01:48,685 --> 01:01:51,017
Keep the right arm straight
with the left elbow.

833
01:01:51,688 --> 01:01:53,349
Check your aim again.

834
01:01:53,857 --> 01:01:55,586
Then whenever you're ready.

835
01:02:22,118 --> 01:02:24,052
You do this all the time?

836
01:02:24,287 --> 01:02:26,050
Whenever I can.

837
01:02:26,623 --> 01:02:29,456
I find it deeply satisfying.

838
01:02:36,299 --> 01:02:37,493
Nice.

839
01:02:38,735 --> 01:02:40,066
You try again.

840
01:02:46,209 --> 01:02:47,574
Take your time.

841
01:02:48,545 --> 01:02:50,069
Don't be afraid. It's safe...

842
01:02:50,280 --> 01:02:52,908
...just as long as you're careful.
It's all about...

843
01:02:53,216 --> 01:02:54,274
...staying relaxed.

844
01:02:56,052 --> 01:02:57,144
Sorry.

845
01:02:58,488 --> 01:02:59,648
It's okay.

846
01:03:02,659 --> 01:03:04,149
Just relax.

847
01:03:07,163 --> 01:03:08,721
Bend this a little.

848
01:03:08,932 --> 01:03:10,593
Keep this straight.

849
01:03:12,168 --> 01:03:13,499
Hips back a little.

850
01:03:14,170 --> 01:03:15,660
Lean into it.

851
01:03:17,607 --> 01:03:19,006
Commit to it.

852
01:03:22,779 --> 01:03:24,337
Check your aim again.

853
01:03:26,783 --> 01:03:28,011
Relax...

854
01:03:29,119 --> 01:03:30,450
...and fire.

855
01:03:36,526 --> 01:03:37,788
There you go.

856
01:03:39,028 --> 01:03:40,518
Doesn't that feel good?

857
01:03:48,471 --> 01:03:50,701
- Want to try the shotgun?
- Sure.

858
01:04:07,557 --> 01:04:09,991
You want to stay at my place tonight?

859
01:04:12,395 --> 01:04:15,922
I mean, you don't have to.
But the couch folds out.

860
01:04:17,901 --> 01:04:20,369
I just thought it'd be silly
to go to my place...

861
01:04:20,637 --> 01:04:24,733
...then you'd have to drive across town
to some crummy old motel.

862
01:04:32,415 --> 01:04:34,042
That'd be great.

863
01:04:34,250 --> 01:04:35,342
Good.

864
01:04:36,686 --> 01:04:40,520
I'll even give you a receipt.
You can write it off.

865
01:04:41,558 --> 01:04:43,287
You know my motto:

866
01:04:45,361 --> 01:04:47,420
Always save the receipt.

867
01:05:00,710 --> 01:05:02,109
You slept at her house?

868
01:05:03,613 --> 01:05:05,410
She thought it'd be easier...

869
01:05:05,648 --> 01:05:07,741
...than driving back to the motel.

870
01:05:07,951 --> 01:05:10,078
I can't believe you slept at her house.

871
01:05:10,286 --> 01:05:12,584
I can't believe,
with all that time with her...

872
01:05:12,789 --> 01:05:15,724
...I couldn't tell more
what was going on in her head.

873
01:05:16,059 --> 01:05:18,289
I couldn't tell what she
was thinking.

874
01:05:19,229 --> 01:05:22,130
That's usually how it is
in the beginning.

875
01:05:24,300 --> 01:05:27,565
Maybe I'll be able to see more
tonight at dinner.

876
01:05:29,138 --> 01:05:30,799
You're taking her to dinner.

877
01:05:31,140 --> 01:05:33,074
What was I going to say, no?

878
01:05:33,409 --> 01:05:35,377
You got anymore on Kragen Vincent?

879
01:05:35,578 --> 01:05:38,706
There's one serving time
at the State Penitentiary.

880
01:05:38,915 --> 01:05:42,112
A life sentence.
Prison records didn't say what for.

881
01:05:42,318 --> 01:05:45,151
We better go find out. Anything else?

882
01:05:46,589 --> 01:05:47,749
What is it?

883
01:05:48,591 --> 01:05:49,649
Nothing.

884
01:06:10,913 --> 01:06:12,972
You the officer in charge of records?

885
01:06:13,182 --> 01:06:15,241
I'm him. Lieutenant Earl Hagans.

886
01:06:15,551 --> 01:06:18,645
- Steve Arlo. Can I come in?
- What is this regarding?

887
01:06:18,855 --> 01:06:20,152
I work for a private...

888
01:06:20,390 --> 01:06:24,486
The Department does not share records
with P.I. S except by court order.

889
01:06:24,727 --> 01:06:27,491
I assume that you do not have
a court order.

890
01:06:27,697 --> 01:06:29,995
I work for a private detective
named Daryl Zero.

891
01:06:33,970 --> 01:06:36,939
Murder One, in 1972. Single count.

892
01:06:37,573 --> 01:06:39,700
And guess what the victim's name is.

893
01:06:39,909 --> 01:06:40,933
Let me guess.

894
01:06:41,144 --> 01:06:44,443
I don't mean really guess.
No way you could actually guess.

895
01:06:44,647 --> 01:06:46,080
Clarissa.

896
01:06:47,650 --> 01:06:49,743
Yeah. Clarissa Devereau.

897
01:06:50,586 --> 01:06:52,053
Of 'plummeting birds' fame.

898
01:06:52,255 --> 01:06:53,517
Seems likely, doesn't it?

899
01:06:53,756 --> 01:06:54,882
Very likely.

900
01:06:54,924 --> 01:06:58,553
Two shots, one to the head,
one to the torso, execution style.

901
01:06:58,795 --> 01:07:00,126
In her motel room.

902
01:07:00,330 --> 01:07:01,797
Sounds professional.

903
01:07:01,998 --> 01:07:06,401
Except he made a complete mess.
A ton of evidence, prints on everything.

904
01:07:07,670 --> 01:07:09,467
I got crime scene photos.

905
01:07:09,672 --> 01:07:13,631
Remember the case of the hired gun
who made way, way too many mistakes?

906
01:07:14,010 --> 01:07:18,413
It's a lot like that. They pick him up,
try him, give him life, no parole.

907
01:07:18,614 --> 01:07:20,809
They think he works for someone
but he won't talk...

908
01:07:21,050 --> 01:07:22,881
...even when they offer him a deal.

909
01:07:23,086 --> 01:07:26,146
And Clarissa has quite
an arrest record for a young girl.

910
01:07:26,522 --> 01:07:28,581
Mostly political, New York and Boston.

911
01:07:28,791 --> 01:07:32,090
Disturbing the peace,
public indecency...

912
01:07:32,295 --> 01:07:33,728
...breaking and entering.

913
01:07:33,963 --> 01:07:35,260
Regular firecracker.

914
01:07:35,465 --> 01:07:37,524
Regular 'plummeting bird.'

915
01:07:39,535 --> 01:07:41,230
And Vincent's still in jail?

916
01:07:41,704 --> 01:07:45,640
No. He was moved for medical reasons
a couple years ago.

917
01:08:08,731 --> 01:08:10,323
<i>Kragen is her father.</i>

918
01:08:11,334 --> 01:08:14,565
She was raised by his sister
because he was in prison.

919
01:08:15,171 --> 01:08:18,334
She blames Stark
for ruining her father's life.

920
01:08:18,775 --> 01:08:22,040
Stark hired Vincent to kill Clarissa...

921
01:08:22,412 --> 01:08:24,039
...for some reason.

922
01:08:24,247 --> 01:08:28,149
Vincent got caught, spent his life
in prison. Now he's dying...

923
01:08:28,351 --> 01:08:30,751
...this slow, painful death.

924
01:08:31,187 --> 01:08:35,590
She's watched her father's life
drip away and she's getting even.

925
01:08:36,025 --> 01:08:38,721
She has something,
some evidence or something...

926
01:08:38,928 --> 01:08:41,362
...that ties Stark to the murder.

927
01:08:41,931 --> 01:08:45,867
I got to figure out what it is
and where she's keeping it.

928
01:08:48,037 --> 01:08:51,200
Take me to the scene of the crime.

929
01:08:54,544 --> 01:08:56,412
It's right up here.

930
01:08:57,046 --> 01:08:59,446
<i>Ready? 1, 2, 3.</i>

931
01:09:03,386 --> 01:09:06,082
The bed we just moved
is a full-size bed.

932
01:09:06,289 --> 01:09:09,417
In 1972, there was no size
called full.

933
01:09:09,625 --> 01:09:11,525
They had doubles and queens.

934
01:09:11,727 --> 01:09:15,094
The full was invented
to combine the width of a queen...

935
01:09:15,298 --> 01:09:18,096
...with the space-efficient
length of a double...

936
01:09:18,301 --> 01:09:21,566
...and eventually replaced the double
in North America and Europe...

937
01:09:21,771 --> 01:09:24,365
...except for Quebec and Sweden.

938
01:09:24,574 --> 01:09:26,974
The bed in the picture...

939
01:09:27,643 --> 01:09:29,133
...is not a double.

940
01:09:29,479 --> 01:09:32,539
It's too long. It's not a full.
It wasn't invented.

941
01:09:32,748 --> 01:09:34,841
It is a queen.

942
01:09:38,087 --> 01:09:42,217
Which means that that bed then
was longer than this bed...

943
01:09:42,425 --> 01:09:43,653
...now.

944
01:09:45,528 --> 01:09:48,986
So sometime in the last 30 years,
somebody must have replaced the bed.

945
01:09:52,602 --> 01:09:53,466
Hear that?

946
01:09:54,604 --> 01:09:55,764
Secret room?

947
01:09:56,672 --> 01:10:00,608
It's a pipe. There once was a radiant
water heater right there.

948
01:10:02,778 --> 01:10:04,473
Kragen bursts into the room.

949
01:10:04,680 --> 01:10:08,912
Her body was found face up. She must've
been facing him, probably standing...

950
01:10:09,118 --> 01:10:11,586
...close to where you are now.

951
01:10:11,787 --> 01:10:14,813
Right away, before she could scream,
she's down...

952
01:10:15,024 --> 01:10:17,185
...she's dead, it's over.

953
01:10:17,793 --> 01:10:20,694
The only question is,
once she was dead...

954
01:10:21,697 --> 01:10:23,790
...why didn't he get out of there?

955
01:10:24,700 --> 01:10:28,261
Instead he proceeds
to touch the dresser, the sink...

956
01:10:28,471 --> 01:10:31,304
...the doorknob and the nightstand.

957
01:10:33,476 --> 01:10:35,706
What does the bed have to do with it?

958
01:10:36,712 --> 01:10:39,510
In 1972, it was against code...

959
01:10:39,715 --> 01:10:43,014
...to have a hotel bed
2 feet from a door that opens inwards...

960
01:10:43,219 --> 01:10:45,210
...7 feet from a fish tank...

961
01:10:45,421 --> 01:10:46,888
...or a lava lamp...

962
01:10:47,156 --> 01:10:50,284
...or 3 feet from a radiant...

963
01:10:50,426 --> 01:10:51,586
...heater.

964
01:10:52,395 --> 01:10:55,956
Imagine if you will,
a bed longer than this one...

965
01:10:56,165 --> 01:10:58,258
...and a heater over here.

966
01:10:58,701 --> 01:10:59,827
Wouldn't clear 2 feet...

967
01:11:00,036 --> 01:11:03,494
...much less 3. And no inspector
would let that pass.

968
01:11:04,440 --> 01:11:05,634
Which means...?

969
01:11:06,108 --> 01:11:07,666
Which means...

970
01:11:10,947 --> 01:11:12,972
...lKragen may have moved the bed.

971
01:11:13,849 --> 01:11:16,147
I see. So you're proposing...

972
01:11:16,419 --> 01:11:18,216
...that he busts in the room...

973
01:11:18,421 --> 01:11:20,946
...sees her standing there,
shoots her twice...

974
01:11:22,124 --> 01:11:23,421
...moves the bed.

975
01:11:23,626 --> 01:11:24,923
Something like that.

976
01:11:25,127 --> 01:11:26,992
Why would anybody do that?

977
01:11:27,229 --> 01:11:29,424
Hello.
I don't know.

978
01:11:29,632 --> 01:11:34,092
I'm trying to figure out some physical
evidence that Kragen might have taken...

979
01:11:34,303 --> 01:11:38,034
...that he gave to his daughter
so that she could blackmail Stark.

980
01:11:38,274 --> 01:11:41,402
I'm trying to figure out what is absent.

981
01:11:42,712 --> 01:11:46,614
Something happened in here. Something
involving his touching the dresser...

982
01:11:46,816 --> 01:11:51,719
...touching the sink, touching the
doorknob, touching the nightstand...

983
01:11:52,989 --> 01:11:54,183
...and probably...

984
01:11:54,390 --> 01:11:55,857
...moving the bed.

985
01:11:56,726 --> 01:11:57,988
Probably?

986
01:11:59,161 --> 01:12:01,129
Somebody else could have moved it.

987
01:12:01,330 --> 01:12:04,231
Come on. There were only
two of them. Him and her.

988
01:12:09,872 --> 01:12:10,702
Exactly.

989
01:12:14,176 --> 01:12:16,076
You need to talk to Stark.

990
01:12:17,246 --> 01:12:19,578
We got a few questions for him.

991
01:12:20,916 --> 01:12:23,544
I had a feeling you two
would be a good match.

992
01:12:23,753 --> 01:12:25,846
I'm good at reading people.

993
01:12:27,923 --> 01:12:29,185
Thank you.

994
01:12:30,426 --> 01:12:32,018
Do you want my opinion?

995
01:12:33,362 --> 01:12:35,057
You should try to hold onto him.

996
01:12:35,264 --> 01:12:39,064
How often do you meet a wealthy single
architect from Los Angeles?

997
01:12:39,869 --> 01:12:42,429
Daisy, he's an accountant.

998
01:12:43,105 --> 01:12:44,436
Are you sure?

999
01:12:45,107 --> 01:12:49,942
He's here for their convention.
That's why I asked him to do my taxes.

1000
01:12:50,212 --> 01:12:52,544
I swear I thought he said
he was an architect.

1001
01:13:09,565 --> 01:13:10,725
Question:

1002
01:13:11,400 --> 01:13:12,867
- Sorry to startle you.
- Jesus.

1003
01:13:13,135 --> 01:13:16,730
How do you pronounce
the word t-o-w-a-r-d-s?

1004
01:13:17,139 --> 01:13:18,868
You nearly gave me a heart attack.

1005
01:13:19,075 --> 01:13:21,134
I had to contact you right away.

1006
01:13:21,644 --> 01:13:22,975
What do you need?

1007
01:13:23,312 --> 01:13:25,746
I must ask you some things.
Just drive.

1008
01:13:25,981 --> 01:13:27,642
Fasten your seat belt.

1009
01:13:29,151 --> 01:13:32,484
First of all, how do you pronounce
the word t-o-w-a-r-d-s?

1010
01:13:33,823 --> 01:13:35,017
Towards?

1011
01:13:35,257 --> 01:13:37,817
And things that have wings and fly?

1012
01:13:38,961 --> 01:13:40,155
You mean birds?

1013
01:13:40,830 --> 01:13:42,559
That's right. They don't rhyme.

1014
01:13:42,765 --> 01:13:43,823
What!?

1015
01:13:44,033 --> 01:13:45,295
Never mind.

1016
01:13:45,501 --> 01:13:47,833
The other thing was,
why did you kill Clarissa?

1017
01:13:50,773 --> 01:13:53,833
I met her my sophomore year.
I was 19...

1018
01:13:54,343 --> 01:13:57,278
...and she was 25, I think.

1019
01:13:57,680 --> 01:14:00,012
From New York, living in Cambridge.

1020
01:14:00,516 --> 01:14:02,609
I met her at a demonstration.

1021
01:14:03,119 --> 01:14:05,781
I have never seen anybody like her.

1022
01:14:06,455 --> 01:14:10,755
She let me walk her home and she
kissed me for the first and only time.

1023
01:14:10,960 --> 01:14:14,794
You can skip right to the part
where you decide to kill her.

1024
01:14:16,699 --> 01:14:18,360
Watch yourself, Arlo.

1025
01:14:19,869 --> 01:14:24,806
Please describe the circumstances
surrounding your contracting her murder.

1026
01:14:30,146 --> 01:14:32,876
After that first night, I was hooked.

1027
01:14:34,550 --> 01:14:36,381
I was like an addict.

1028
01:14:37,720 --> 01:14:40,382
Finally, she didn't want
to see me anymore.

1029
01:14:41,390 --> 01:14:43,483
I guess I got a little obsessive.

1030
01:14:47,062 --> 01:14:50,498
My last year of graduate school
I met my wife.

1031
01:14:51,333 --> 01:14:55,497
And after I graduated, we moved
back here, we got married...

1032
01:14:56,005 --> 01:14:58,906
...and I went to work
with my dad at the company.

1033
01:15:02,578 --> 01:15:05,240
And I had all but forgotten about...

1034
01:15:05,581 --> 01:15:06,912
...Clarissa.

1035
01:15:09,852 --> 01:15:13,015
Then, in 1972,
we'd been back about a year...

1036
01:15:15,591 --> 01:15:17,684
...I got a letter from her.

1037
01:15:19,094 --> 01:15:21,358
She was here in Portland.

1038
01:15:23,432 --> 01:15:24,990
The letter was...

1039
01:15:25,201 --> 01:15:27,431
...a threatening letter.

1040
01:15:29,104 --> 01:15:30,366
What was it?

1041
01:15:32,374 --> 01:15:35,207
I don't think that makes
a thread of difference.

1042
01:15:37,379 --> 01:15:39,609
What did the letter say?

1043
01:15:44,453 --> 01:15:47,115
She was accusing me of something.

1044
01:15:54,063 --> 01:15:55,155
Rape.

1045
01:15:58,234 --> 01:15:59,792
Did she want money?

1046
01:16:00,736 --> 01:16:03,102
No, she wanted to ruin my life.

1047
01:16:03,906 --> 01:16:07,273
I knew no jury'd convict me.
I was convinced of that.

1048
01:16:07,476 --> 01:16:11,105
But I couldn't take this
kind of publicity, nor could my family.

1049
01:16:11,313 --> 01:16:12,610
I saw...

1050
01:16:12,815 --> 01:16:15,579
...my whole future flash before my eyes.

1051
01:16:17,987 --> 01:16:19,955
So you hired Kragen Vincent.

1052
01:16:20,990 --> 01:16:23,652
He said that for $5,000...

1053
01:16:24,093 --> 01:16:26,084
...he could solve my problem.

1054
01:16:30,432 --> 01:16:33,265
And that's all I know
about the subject, officer.

1055
01:16:37,273 --> 01:16:40,106
So what's in the safe deposit box?

1056
01:16:43,178 --> 01:16:44,304
A tape.

1057
01:16:44,513 --> 01:16:47,573
A tape he made of our meeting.
Audio tape.

1058
01:16:47,750 --> 01:16:49,149
My hiring him...

1059
01:16:49,818 --> 01:16:52,412
...our names as clear as day.

1060
01:16:52,755 --> 01:16:54,882
Why didn't you just destroy it...

1061
01:16:55,124 --> 01:16:56,318
...years ago?

1062
01:16:57,092 --> 01:16:59,151
Because I don't know where it is.

1063
01:16:59,762 --> 01:17:00,922
Go on.

1064
01:17:02,097 --> 01:17:04,622
About a week after he gets caught...

1065
01:17:04,833 --> 01:17:07,961
...a man comes to my house
in the middle of the night...

1066
01:17:08,170 --> 01:17:12,607
...and tells me that Kragen expects me
to bankroll his defense...

1067
01:17:13,342 --> 01:17:15,333
...though a middleman, obviously.

1068
01:17:16,111 --> 01:17:17,578
And he also...

1069
01:17:17,780 --> 01:17:19,941
...wanted money for his family.

1070
01:17:21,116 --> 01:17:23,516
Then he played me a copy of this tape...

1071
01:17:24,520 --> 01:17:28,513
...and said if I refused he would
turn the tape over to the police.

1072
01:17:29,291 --> 01:17:30,781
He then gave me...

1073
01:17:31,293 --> 01:17:32,419
...a key to...

1074
01:17:32,628 --> 01:17:34,528
...a safe deposit box.

1075
01:17:34,863 --> 01:17:37,423
Said at the end of 25 years...

1076
01:17:37,633 --> 01:17:40,534
...when Kragen got out
or if he should die...

1077
01:17:40,869 --> 01:17:43,633
...I would be given
the location of the box.

1078
01:17:44,206 --> 01:17:45,969
In the meantime...

1079
01:17:46,809 --> 01:17:48,868
...l'm to hang onto this key...

1080
01:17:49,144 --> 01:17:53,706
...with no lock and our friend
would hang onto his lock with no key.

1081
01:17:55,651 --> 01:17:59,246
What would you do if someone was
threatening you like that...

1082
01:17:59,488 --> 01:18:02,423
...or blackmailing you like this?
What do you do?

1083
01:18:03,559 --> 01:18:04,685
I don't know.

1084
01:18:04,893 --> 01:18:06,554
It's never come up.

1085
01:18:07,496 --> 01:18:09,123
Imagine it.

1086
01:18:09,331 --> 01:18:10,821
Imagine some...

1087
01:18:11,066 --> 01:18:12,465
...opportunistic...

1088
01:18:12,668 --> 01:18:14,636
...piece of birdshit...

1089
01:18:14,837 --> 01:18:17,169
...has got a way to compromise you.

1090
01:18:18,073 --> 01:18:22,305
What do you do about it? You can't
buy silence. You can only rent it.

1091
01:18:22,511 --> 01:18:25,742
If somebody has something on you,
they'll always have it.

1092
01:18:26,081 --> 01:18:28,174
So the cost has no ceiling...

1093
01:18:30,252 --> 01:18:32,186
...and the fear has no end.

1094
01:18:35,591 --> 01:18:36,751
That's why...

1095
01:18:37,359 --> 01:18:40,260
...some knowledge, some information...

1096
01:18:42,531 --> 01:18:44,590
...is like a terminal disease.

1097
01:18:47,202 --> 01:18:48,362
It's...

1098
01:18:49,104 --> 01:18:50,401
...contagious...

1099
01:18:50,606 --> 01:18:52,039
...and it's fatal.

1100
01:18:56,779 --> 01:18:59,612
<i>Passion is the enemy of precision.</i>

1101
01:18:59,948 --> 01:19:02,678
<i>Forget the misnomer 'crime of passion. '</i>

1102
01:19:02,885 --> 01:19:07,015
<i>All crime is passionate. It's passion
that moves the criminal to act...</i>

1103
01:19:07,222 --> 01:19:10,555
<i>... that disrupts the static inertia
of morality.</i>

1104
01:19:10,793 --> 01:19:15,423
<i>The client's passion for this dead
woman had facilitated his downfall.</i>

1105
01:19:15,631 --> 01:19:17,531
<i>And the blackmailer's passion...</i>

1106
01:19:17,733 --> 01:19:19,530
<i>... would facilitate hers.</i>

1107
01:19:22,171 --> 01:19:23,934
<i>When you live with no passion...</i>

1108
01:19:24,139 --> 01:19:27,700
<i>... other people's passions
come into glaring relief.</i>

1109
01:19:27,910 --> 01:19:29,207
Bullshit, bullshit...

1110
01:19:29,411 --> 01:19:30,503
...bullshit!

1111
01:19:30,746 --> 01:19:33,078
Jesus! Would you stop it?

1112
01:19:34,450 --> 01:19:35,542
Stop it!

1113
01:19:35,751 --> 01:19:36,718
Jesus!

1114
01:19:36,919 --> 01:19:38,614
Control yourself, all right?

1115
01:19:38,821 --> 01:19:40,618
Control myself?

1116
01:19:40,823 --> 01:19:43,485
This is fucking bullshit!

1117
01:19:44,259 --> 01:19:47,558
Haven't I been good to you?
Haven't I been fucking incredibly...

1118
01:19:47,763 --> 01:19:52,462
...mindblowingly, fuckingly, divinely
generous as a fucking saint...

1119
01:19:52,734 --> 01:19:54,167
...you ungrateful fuck!

1120
01:19:54,770 --> 01:19:55,794
Hey, watch it...

1121
01:19:56,071 --> 01:19:57,060
...all right?

1122
01:19:57,272 --> 01:19:59,069
Ungrateful fuck!

1123
01:19:59,374 --> 01:20:00,500
Shut up!

1124
01:20:02,511 --> 01:20:03,842
Why?

1125
01:20:05,781 --> 01:20:08,545
I told you why.
I cannot live like this anymore.

1126
01:20:08,750 --> 01:20:11,981
I can't do it to Jess.
I can't do it to myself...

1127
01:20:12,187 --> 01:20:15,520
...and I'm sick and tired of working
for the Starks of the world...

1128
01:20:15,958 --> 01:20:19,587
...the lowest scum of the earth, buying
their way out of their own messes.

1129
01:20:19,795 --> 01:20:23,856
These people are victims of plots
and they need our help.

1130
01:20:24,800 --> 01:20:28,702
This guy is a murderer-at-large
who needs our help.

1131
01:20:29,805 --> 01:20:33,172
Their business equals their business.

1132
01:20:33,375 --> 01:20:36,105
We're not involved.
It has nothing to do...

1133
01:20:36,345 --> 01:20:37,277
...with us.

1134
01:20:37,479 --> 01:20:38,776
Do you believe that?

1135
01:20:39,314 --> 01:20:41,509
We're the good guys.

1136
01:20:42,818 --> 01:20:44,683
What are you talking about?

1137
01:20:44,887 --> 01:20:47,151
There aren't any good guys.

1138
01:20:47,656 --> 01:20:49,783
You realize that, don't you?

1139
01:20:49,992 --> 01:20:54,019
You realize there aren't evil guys
and innocent guys.

1140
01:20:56,732 --> 01:20:59,826
It's just a bunch of guys.

1141
01:21:03,071 --> 01:21:04,868
What am I supposed to do?

1142
01:21:07,075 --> 01:21:10,044
Just start taking meetings with people?

1143
01:21:12,014 --> 01:21:14,505
Just start talking with people?

1144
01:21:15,350 --> 01:21:16,578
Maybe.

1145
01:21:19,254 --> 01:21:20,744
Fuck that.

1146
01:21:25,194 --> 01:21:27,185
You know, you'll figure it out.

1147
01:21:28,363 --> 01:21:29,387
I mean...

1148
01:21:29,598 --> 01:21:31,395
...you're probably the best...

1149
01:21:31,600 --> 01:21:32,567
Excuse me?

1150
01:21:34,436 --> 01:21:37,064
Excuse me. You are the best.

1151
01:21:38,207 --> 01:21:40,573
I'm telling you that after this case...

1152
01:21:42,711 --> 01:21:44,269
...l'm finished.

1153
01:21:50,052 --> 01:21:51,713
I meant...

1154
01:21:52,721 --> 01:21:55,053
...what am I supposed to do...

1155
01:21:57,559 --> 01:21:59,550
...without you?

1156
01:22:08,403 --> 01:22:10,394
You want my honest opinion?

1157
01:22:13,141 --> 01:22:16,577
You should take all this money
that you've made...

1158
01:22:17,579 --> 01:22:19,240
...and move to Europe.

1159
01:22:19,915 --> 01:22:21,815
Meet a girl.

1160
01:22:22,751 --> 01:22:27,654
See the world. Really see the world.
Don't observe it. See what it's like.

1161
01:22:31,927 --> 01:22:33,588
What do you know?

1162
01:22:36,765 --> 01:22:39,563
I'm the greatest private investigator...

1163
01:22:39,768 --> 01:22:41,429
...in the world.

1164
01:22:56,952 --> 01:23:01,082
I'll go check for safe deposit boxes
under the name Kragen Vincent.

1165
01:23:01,723 --> 01:23:03,384
I don't know if that's necessary.

1166
01:23:05,193 --> 01:23:07,821
What Clearburg probably
meant when he says...

1167
01:23:08,030 --> 01:23:11,261
...there's no boxer with the name
Kragen Vincent...

1168
01:23:11,466 --> 01:23:13,058
...is that there's no boxes...

1169
01:23:13,802 --> 01:23:17,203
...with the name Kragen Vincent.
I think it's a typo.

1170
01:23:18,307 --> 01:23:20,207
Right. Right.

1171
01:23:21,376 --> 01:23:23,367
He probably used a different name.

1172
01:23:25,047 --> 01:23:26,810
That's what I think.

1173
01:23:27,649 --> 01:23:29,173
Well, then...

1174
01:23:29,384 --> 01:23:32,217
...l'll go get a beer
with my friend Bill.

1175
01:23:32,888 --> 01:23:34,515
I said, I think.

1176
01:23:35,390 --> 01:23:38,689
But you should go and check
just to make sure.

1177
01:23:41,396 --> 01:23:42,556
Fine.

1178
01:23:44,066 --> 01:23:46,534
But I really hope that you've heard me.

1179
01:24:00,849 --> 01:24:02,407
Sorry to startle you.

1180
01:24:03,518 --> 01:24:05,076
What are you doing here?

1181
01:24:05,554 --> 01:24:06,486
I followed you.

1182
01:24:08,523 --> 01:24:10,684
Back at my car,
this was on the windshield.

1183
01:24:10,892 --> 01:24:12,883
Another payment,
due tomorrow morning.

1184
01:24:14,262 --> 01:24:16,025
You sure you weren't followed?

1185
01:24:16,231 --> 01:24:17,596
I wasn't.

1186
01:24:18,200 --> 01:24:20,395
I told you how to contact me.

1187
01:24:20,602 --> 01:24:22,331
You should not have come here.

1188
01:24:22,537 --> 01:24:23,834
Is he in there?

1189
01:24:24,039 --> 01:24:27,907
If I walked in there now,
would Mr. Zero be happy to meet me?

1190
01:24:29,511 --> 01:24:30,603
Go home.

1191
01:24:31,113 --> 01:24:34,844
Right now. Make the payment tomorrow.
We're very, very close.

1192
01:24:35,050 --> 01:24:36,847
I'm sick of cooperating.

1193
01:24:37,152 --> 01:24:41,521
It used to be 2 or 3 weeks. Now it's
every two days. Why so close together?

1194
01:24:41,790 --> 01:24:46,284
Maybe he's nervous. Maybe he wants
to kill me. I should carry a weapon.

1195
01:24:47,662 --> 01:24:49,129
No, you shouldn't.

1196
01:24:49,731 --> 01:24:51,460
Look, just don't panic...

1197
01:24:51,666 --> 01:24:52,724
...all right?

1198
01:24:54,002 --> 01:24:55,492
How dedicated are you, really?

1199
01:24:57,239 --> 01:24:59,332
Your timing's impeccable.

1200
01:25:00,008 --> 01:25:02,135
- How do you mean?
- Never mind.

1201
01:25:03,245 --> 01:25:06,646
Maybe you've got some ambition
of your own. Maybe you want...

1202
01:25:06,848 --> 01:25:08,281
...to have your own firm.

1203
01:25:08,917 --> 01:25:12,717
You got me pegged. That's all I want
is to someday be Daryl Zero.

1204
01:25:13,355 --> 01:25:16,188
I'll give you $ 1 million
if you sell out your boss.

1205
01:25:16,691 --> 01:25:18,716
Just turn over your suspect.

1206
01:25:18,927 --> 01:25:20,758
Name and address.

1207
01:25:23,098 --> 01:25:24,565
$ 2 million...

1208
01:25:24,766 --> 01:25:27,257
...for a name and an address.

1209
01:25:27,536 --> 01:25:29,868
Cash.
We can go to the bank right now.

1210
01:25:30,439 --> 01:25:34,432
You'd give me $ 2 million so you
don't have to do this thing tomorrow?

1211
01:25:35,310 --> 01:25:37,039
I'm willing to give you $5 million.

1212
01:25:37,612 --> 01:25:39,443
How much does he pay you?

1213
01:25:40,549 --> 01:25:42,244
$5 million...

1214
01:25:42,451 --> 01:25:46,114
...so you can kill someone right away
instead of a day later.

1215
01:25:46,421 --> 01:25:47,513
For $5 million...

1216
01:25:47,722 --> 01:25:49,121
...you do it.

1217
01:25:57,299 --> 01:26:00,427
- What if I walked in right now...
- He's not in there.

1218
01:26:00,735 --> 01:26:02,396
What if I want to find out myself?

1219
01:26:03,071 --> 01:26:04,561
What would happen?

1220
01:26:05,240 --> 01:26:06,537
I'll shoot you.

1221
01:26:08,643 --> 01:26:10,577
Really. I will.

1222
01:26:11,913 --> 01:26:13,813
I have a gun and everything.

1223
01:26:17,152 --> 01:26:18,380
You're threatening me?

1224
01:26:20,422 --> 01:26:22,083
I'm threatening to kill you.

1225
01:27:32,327 --> 01:27:33,385
What?

1226
01:27:33,995 --> 01:27:36,327
Right before you jump off the plane...

1227
01:27:37,899 --> 01:27:40,527
...you stand there
with all the equipment on.

1228
01:27:40,735 --> 01:27:42,760
You know what to do,
you can't wait.

1229
01:27:43,004 --> 01:27:46,132
Is there a time when you think:

1230
01:27:46,341 --> 01:27:49,970
"What if it doesn't open? What if this
is the last thing I ever do?"

1231
01:27:50,178 --> 01:27:52,840
You're really stuck
on the skydiving thing.

1232
01:27:55,584 --> 01:27:58,917
I'm stuck on what it is that makes you
do very dangerous things.

1233
01:27:59,254 --> 01:28:02,587
Even dangerous things
can be safe if you're careful.

1234
01:28:03,358 --> 01:28:05,383
There's such a thing as
knowing the odds.

1235
01:28:05,594 --> 01:28:07,528
Quitting while you're ahead.

1236
01:28:08,863 --> 01:28:10,854
Quitting before you're dead.

1237
01:28:17,772 --> 01:28:20,366
You know, you, me...

1238
01:28:21,443 --> 01:28:26,380
...anyone could walk out here and
get killed by some drunk in a pickup.

1239
01:28:28,717 --> 01:28:31,777
I could slip in the shower
and break my neck.

1240
01:28:32,053 --> 01:28:34,385
When your number's up it's up.

1241
01:28:35,724 --> 01:28:38,887
There's no sense to it.
There's no justice.

1242
01:28:40,795 --> 01:28:42,592
Innocent people suffer...

1243
01:28:42,797 --> 01:28:45,129
...and murderers get away with it.

1244
01:28:45,967 --> 01:28:50,631
So when my number's up,
whether I'm walking down the street...

1245
01:28:54,743 --> 01:28:56,734
...or doing something else...

1246
01:28:57,145 --> 01:28:58,908
...that will be that.

1247
01:29:01,816 --> 01:29:05,081
And until then, I'm just going to do
what I need to do.

1248
01:29:07,656 --> 01:29:09,749
What is it you need to do?

1249
01:29:12,494 --> 01:29:13,984
I need...

1250
01:29:15,997 --> 01:29:17,828
...to try to feel right.

1251
01:29:20,268 --> 01:29:21,735
Can I get you anything else?

1252
01:29:21,936 --> 01:29:23,528
No, I think that's it.

1253
01:29:24,172 --> 01:29:25,662
Do you need anything?

1254
01:29:26,107 --> 01:29:27,438
I'm okay.

1255
01:29:28,677 --> 01:29:29,837
I'll take the check.

1256
01:29:30,345 --> 01:29:32,279
You got it. Be right back.

1257
01:29:33,615 --> 01:29:35,344
When I was a little girl...

1258
01:29:36,618 --> 01:29:40,679
...I used to hope that someday
I'd grow up to look like that waitress.

1259
01:29:46,628 --> 01:29:48,858
My mother had hair like that.

1260
01:29:51,132 --> 01:29:52,656
My natural mother.

1261
01:29:54,035 --> 01:29:55,195
Really?

1262
01:30:16,157 --> 01:30:18,523
God, I forgot how that works.
Wait a minute.

1263
01:30:18,727 --> 01:30:22,925
Can a person be considered
physical evidence? Like in a rape case?

1264
01:30:23,998 --> 01:30:26,660
You mean if the guy
doesn't know about the kid?

1265
01:30:29,337 --> 01:30:30,304
I think so.

1266
01:30:30,839 --> 01:30:32,568
We think so. Why?

1267
01:30:34,542 --> 01:30:35,440
You mean...

1268
01:30:35,844 --> 01:30:38,142
She is the evidence.

1269
01:30:38,346 --> 01:30:40,507
She's not Kragen's daughter.

1270
01:30:42,684 --> 01:30:44,413
She's Stark's daughter.

1271
01:30:52,527 --> 01:30:55,087
I must admit, I like this place.

1272
01:31:03,772 --> 01:31:04,932
What?

1273
01:31:05,607 --> 01:31:08,599
You said that you don't
speak to your family.

1274
01:31:11,446 --> 01:31:12,708
Why not?

1275
01:31:14,382 --> 01:31:16,543
I realize I'm prying...

1276
01:31:17,051 --> 01:31:19,042
...but what can I say? I'm prying.

1277
01:31:19,721 --> 01:31:21,450
I want to know about you.

1278
01:31:34,636 --> 01:31:37,298
Just look me in the eyes and talk to me.

1279
01:31:41,910 --> 01:31:43,070
All right.

1280
01:31:52,420 --> 01:31:54,479
My father was...

1281
01:31:55,590 --> 01:31:58,252
...an evil, abusive man.

1282
01:32:02,831 --> 01:32:04,822
And he killed my mother...

1283
01:32:06,100 --> 01:32:08,159
...when she was sleeping.

1284
01:32:09,938 --> 01:32:11,132
And then...

1285
01:32:11,339 --> 01:32:13,273
...he slit his wrists...

1286
01:32:14,843 --> 01:32:16,140
...when I was...

1287
01:32:16,344 --> 01:32:17,675
...13.

1288
01:32:29,023 --> 01:32:31,184
I don't talk about that...

1289
01:32:34,295 --> 01:32:35,455
...much.

1290
01:32:36,030 --> 01:32:38,464
I used to when it happened...

1291
01:32:39,701 --> 01:32:42,135
...and then one day I woke up...

1292
01:32:43,371 --> 01:32:44,463
...and...

1293
01:32:46,140 --> 01:32:47,471
...I don't know.

1294
01:32:50,478 --> 01:32:52,469
Everything was different.

1295
01:33:00,555 --> 01:33:02,147
How about that?

1296
01:33:08,162 --> 01:33:10,892
What doesn't kill you defines you.

1297
01:33:27,115 --> 01:33:32,348
<i>I don't believe in
an interventionist God</i>

1298
01:33:37,692 --> 01:33:40,183
<i>But I know darling...</i>

1299
01:33:40,528 --> 01:33:42,758
<i>... that you do</i>

1300
01:33:48,436 --> 01:33:50,404
<i>But if I did...</i>

1301
01:33:50,605 --> 01:33:53,938
<i>... I would kneel down and ask Him</i>

1302
01:33:58,613 --> 01:34:01,081
Not to intervene...

1303
01:34:01,282 --> 01:34:03,944
...when it came to you

1304
01:34:06,220 --> 01:34:09,587
<i>Or not to touch a hair in your head</i>

1305
01:34:09,791 --> 01:34:11,918
<i>Leave you as you are</i>

1306
01:34:12,126 --> 01:34:14,560
<i>If he felt he had to direct you</i>

1307
01:34:14,796 --> 01:34:17,287
<i>Then direct you into my arms</i>

1308
01:34:51,666 --> 01:34:55,193
Sometimes what you're looking
for is right in front of your nose.

1309
01:34:59,507 --> 01:35:01,600
That's what I've always said.

1310
01:35:32,707 --> 01:35:36,700
You just going to stand there watching
or you going to do something about it?

1311
01:35:51,726 --> 01:35:56,720
<i>And I don't believe
in the existence of angels</i>

1312
01:36:01,903 --> 01:36:03,632
<i>But looking at you...</i>

1313
01:36:03,838 --> 01:36:06,568
<i>... I wonder if that's true</i>

1314
01:36:12,346 --> 01:36:14,143
<i>But if I did...</i>

1315
01:36:14,348 --> 01:36:16,908
<i>... I would summon them together</i>

1316
01:36:22,690 --> 01:36:27,650
<i>And ask them to watch over you</i>

1317
01:36:46,614 --> 01:36:48,104
I got to get going.

1318
01:36:56,290 --> 01:36:59,384
So I'll see you around 6:00
at my place.

1319
01:37:02,063 --> 01:37:04,429
As soon as I'm done with my meetings.

1320
01:37:04,632 --> 01:37:05,724
Good.

1321
01:37:07,902 --> 01:37:09,130
Bye.

1322
01:37:14,742 --> 01:37:18,735
<i>At this point, you will receive
a final message on the pager.</i>

1323
01:37:18,980 --> 01:37:22,814
<i>Get on the corresponding bus
and take it to the end of the line.</i>

1324
01:37:23,251 --> 01:37:25,719
<i>Find the nearby bank of outhouses.</i>

1325
01:37:25,920 --> 01:37:29,879
<i>In center unit, find pair
of blue plastic garbage bags.</i>

1326
01:37:30,091 --> 01:37:32,321
<i>Make your deposit as usual.</i>

1327
01:37:41,769 --> 01:37:44,567
<i>When you have done this
get back on the bus.</i>

1328
01:37:44,772 --> 01:37:48,765
<i>Do not hesitate. Do not deviate
from the designated course.</i>

1329
01:37:49,343 --> 01:37:51,038
<i>You'll be monitored
at every interval.</i>

1330
01:37:51,946 --> 01:37:54,107
<i>We are prepared to act.</i>

1331
01:37:55,716 --> 01:37:58,981
<i>The words were similar but there was
a new component this time:</i>

1332
01:38:00,188 --> 01:38:01,382
<i>Desperation.</i>

1333
01:38:01,722 --> 01:38:04,452
<i>When you spend enough time around
the chemistry of desperation...</i>

1334
01:38:04,659 --> 01:38:06,593
<i>... you come to recognize the smell.</i>

1335
01:38:09,197 --> 01:38:11,427
<i>One desperate element is combustible.</i>

1336
01:38:11,632 --> 01:38:14,533
<i>More than one desperate element
is lethal.</i>

1337
01:38:52,907 --> 01:38:54,238
Shit.

1338
01:39:30,544 --> 01:39:32,535
Call 911. Hurry up.

1339
01:39:32,947 --> 01:39:34,039
All right.

1340
01:40:12,253 --> 01:40:13,220
Are you okay?

1341
01:40:14,755 --> 01:40:16,484
Do you know your name?

1342
01:40:17,425 --> 01:40:18,357
Who are you?

1343
01:40:19,760 --> 01:40:22,320
That's right, sir. Who are you?
You know?

1344
01:40:26,167 --> 01:40:28,397
- What happened?
- Cardiac arrest.

1345
01:40:28,936 --> 01:40:30,335
Are you a doctor?

1346
01:40:46,454 --> 01:40:48,786
<i>What's the name on that box, sir?</i>

1347
01:40:49,023 --> 01:40:50,650
<i>The name is Stark.</i>

1348
01:40:50,858 --> 01:40:52,689
<i>Gloria Stark.</i>

1349
01:40:53,294 --> 01:40:57,628
<i>According to our records, nobody's
been to that box for more than 20 years.</i>

1350
01:40:58,632 --> 01:41:00,463
<i>She lost the key.</i>

1351
01:41:01,369 --> 01:41:02,961
<i>Her father had it.</i>

1352
01:42:35,596 --> 01:42:38,156
<i>Hi, it's Gloria. I'll call you back.</i>

1353
01:42:40,501 --> 01:42:41,832
<i>Are you there?</i>

1354
01:42:55,683 --> 01:42:57,014
I'm here.

1355
01:42:59,353 --> 01:43:02,516
<i>I'm about to get on a plane
and be gone forever.</i>

1356
01:43:06,794 --> 01:43:08,887
I think that's a mistake.

1357
01:43:10,631 --> 01:43:13,191
Yeah, I don't see any choice.

1358
01:43:14,301 --> 01:43:16,132
<i>What if I come find you?</i>

1359
01:43:17,304 --> 01:43:19,534
<i>You're so sure that you could?</i>

1360
01:43:20,708 --> 01:43:23,768
<i>Thai Air. Flight 214.
Direct to Bangkok.</i>

1361
01:43:23,978 --> 01:43:25,809
<i>Departs in half an hour.</i>

1362
01:43:32,987 --> 01:43:34,818
Okay, it's over.

1363
01:43:35,489 --> 01:43:37,116
You figured me out.

1364
01:43:37,324 --> 01:43:39,155
Nobody else got close.

1365
01:43:39,827 --> 01:43:41,988
You know, he doesn't know about you.

1366
01:43:43,063 --> 01:43:45,031
He doesn't know he has a child.

1367
01:43:45,299 --> 01:43:46,357
<i>I know.</i>

1368
01:43:46,567 --> 01:43:48,398
<i>She never told him.</i>

1369
01:43:48,702 --> 01:43:51,262
She wanted him to deny
that he'd even touched her.

1370
01:43:51,472 --> 01:43:55,067
Then at the last minute, surprise!
Look who's a daddy.

1371
01:43:56,243 --> 01:43:58,575
And a rapist. And a murderer.

1372
01:44:02,349 --> 01:44:04,874
He hires Kragen Vincent.

1373
01:44:05,252 --> 01:44:08,881
<i>Kragen decides to hit her
in her motel room late at night.</i>

1374
01:44:09,089 --> 01:44:10,613
<i>He comes in the room...</i>

1375
01:44:10,991 --> 01:44:12,219
<i>... shoots her twice.</i>

1376
01:44:12,426 --> 01:44:17,659
<i>But he doesn't realize that you,
less than a year old, are in the room.</i>

1377
01:44:17,865 --> 01:44:20,891
<i>He doesn't see you at first,
because you're in a crawl space...</i>

1378
01:44:21,101 --> 01:44:25,003
...she's made for you by pulling the
corner of the bed closer to the wall.

1379
01:44:25,205 --> 01:44:29,574
<i>And even with the silencer on the gun,
and it all happening so quickly...</i>

1380
01:44:29,777 --> 01:44:31,335
<i>... you start crying.</i>

1381
01:44:31,545 --> 01:44:34,708
<i>He's got to do something.
You're screaming your lungs out now.</i>

1382
01:44:36,383 --> 01:44:39,375
<i>So he picks you up.
You stop crying.</i>

1383
01:44:40,387 --> 01:44:42,184
<i>And once he's got the baby...</i>

1384
01:44:42,389 --> 01:44:44,050
<i>... it's a done deal.</i>

1385
01:44:44,291 --> 01:44:45,883
<i>There he is...</i>

1386
01:44:46,293 --> 01:44:47,760
<i>... holding the infant.</i>

1387
01:44:47,962 --> 01:44:49,862
<i>That's when he decides...</i>

1388
01:44:50,064 --> 01:44:51,895
<i>... he'd rather risk it all.</i>

1389
01:44:52,399 --> 01:44:56,597
<i>He'd rather risk life in prison
than leave you in that room.</i>

1390
01:44:57,004 --> 01:45:00,030
<i>To protect you from Stark,
he gets rid of all the evidence.</i>

1391
01:45:00,274 --> 01:45:02,435
Diapers, diaper bag...

1392
01:45:02,710 --> 01:45:04,200
...bottles, blankets...

1393
01:45:04,511 --> 01:45:06,843
<i>... something on the dresser,
something in the sink...</i>

1394
01:45:07,047 --> 01:45:08,776
<i>... something hanging off a doorknob...</i>

1395
01:45:08,983 --> 01:45:10,575
<i>... something on the nightstand.</i>

1396
01:45:10,784 --> 01:45:13,344
And then he leaves his prints
everywhere.

1397
01:45:13,821 --> 01:45:17,052
<i>He leaves the body, takes the baby
and hauls ass out of there...</i>

1398
01:45:17,291 --> 01:45:20,055
<i>... because he knows he's got to
get you to his sister.</i>

1399
01:45:20,260 --> 01:45:22,820
You grow up thinking
Vincent is your father...

1400
01:45:23,030 --> 01:45:25,430
...and you're being raised
by your aunt and uncle.

1401
01:45:25,933 --> 01:45:26,797
<i>And then...</i>

1402
01:45:27,001 --> 01:45:28,935
<i>... Vincent comes clean.</i>

1403
01:45:29,169 --> 01:45:33,003
He told me what happened,
but he would never tell me who it was.

1404
01:45:33,507 --> 01:45:34,974
And then about...

1405
01:45:35,175 --> 01:45:39,009
...a year ago, I figured that out.
Mr. Stark.

1406
01:45:40,347 --> 01:45:42,747
So then you start writing letters.

1407
01:45:42,950 --> 01:45:45,783
Stark pays and the rest is history.

1408
01:45:47,955 --> 01:45:49,855
You got the whole thing.

1409
01:45:50,958 --> 01:45:52,357
You win.

1410
01:45:56,864 --> 01:45:59,025
<i>You saved his life this morning.</i>

1411
01:46:00,200 --> 01:46:01,462
I know.

1412
01:46:02,536 --> 01:46:05,630
I guess a person
can't escape their nature.

1413
01:46:07,708 --> 01:46:09,471
<i>How did you know...</i>

1414
01:46:09,810 --> 01:46:11,300
<i>... about me?</i>

1415
01:46:12,880 --> 01:46:14,643
Couple of things.

1416
01:46:16,150 --> 01:46:18,118
<i>And the receipt last night.</i>

1417
01:46:18,318 --> 01:46:19,478
I know.

1418
01:46:19,987 --> 01:46:21,716
I forgot to take it.

1419
01:46:23,323 --> 01:46:26,315
"Passion is the enemy of precision."

1420
01:46:30,497 --> 01:46:32,158
I got sloppy.

1421
01:46:37,404 --> 01:46:39,497
Are you going
to come looking for me?

1422
01:46:41,408 --> 01:46:46,175
Will you tell him about me so he can
have somebody kill me? Because he will.

1423
01:46:46,680 --> 01:46:47,874
<i>I know.</i>

1424
01:46:48,415 --> 01:46:50,747
<i>So what are we going to do about this?</i>

1425
01:46:52,453 --> 01:46:55,980
There's a man sitting on a bench
behind you.

1426
01:46:57,558 --> 01:46:58,320
Oh, God!

1427
01:46:58,525 --> 01:46:59,617
It's okay.

1428
01:47:00,527 --> 01:47:01,926
Relax.

1429
01:47:02,696 --> 01:47:04,061
He has an envelope.

1430
01:47:04,598 --> 01:47:09,035
<i>Inside are some fake identification
and some plane tickets.</i>

1431
01:47:09,269 --> 01:47:12,363
First Ecuador,
and then wherever you want.

1432
01:47:13,440 --> 01:47:15,499
Keep moving, first couple of months.

1433
01:47:15,709 --> 01:47:18,837
Stay out of westernized countries
for a while.

1434
01:47:19,113 --> 01:47:21,741
<i>Don't carry too much cash on your body.</i>

1435
01:47:22,049 --> 01:47:23,846
Give incorrect information...

1436
01:47:24,051 --> 01:47:25,450
...everywhere.

1437
01:47:26,220 --> 01:47:28,450
And never use your real name.

1438
01:47:33,727 --> 01:47:34,955
Thank you.

1439
01:47:37,898 --> 01:47:39,126
Thank you.

1440
01:47:40,567 --> 01:47:41,898
<i>If you knew I was here...</i>

1441
01:47:42,102 --> 01:47:44,070
...why didn't you come yourself?

1442
01:47:45,572 --> 01:47:47,267
<i>I'm not sure.</i>

1443
01:47:48,575 --> 01:47:50,475
I knew you'd be there...

1444
01:47:52,746 --> 01:47:54,976
...but I'd hoped you'd be here.

1445
01:47:56,817 --> 01:47:59,251
<i>You know, you could join me.</i>

1446
01:48:07,661 --> 01:48:09,492
A person can't escape...

1447
01:48:09,830 --> 01:48:11,320
...their nature.

1448
01:48:18,005 --> 01:48:19,939
That's what I thought.

1449
01:48:23,277 --> 01:48:25,268
<i>You're the best I've ever seen.</i>

1450
01:48:30,951 --> 01:48:32,509
So are you.

1451
01:48:39,526 --> 01:48:42,461
I've never said the words before...

1452
01:48:45,465 --> 01:48:46,830
...to anyone.

1453
01:48:49,870 --> 01:48:51,462
You don't have to.

1454
01:48:53,140 --> 01:48:54,971
I love you too...

1455
01:48:56,210 --> 01:48:57,871
<i>... Daryl Zero.</i>

1456
01:49:13,160 --> 01:49:16,186
<i>So ends my account
of the case that I have named...</i>

1457
01:49:16,396 --> 01:49:19,524
<i>"...The Case of the Man Who Got So
Stressed-Out Over His Lost Keys...</i>

1458
01:49:19,733 --> 01:49:21,963
<i>... That He Eventually Had
a Heart Attack...</i>

1459
01:49:22,169 --> 01:49:24,637
<i>... And It Turned Out
They Were in the Sofa All Along. "</i>

1460
01:49:25,339 --> 01:49:27,637
<i>I returned the first installment
of my fee...</i>

1461
01:49:27,875 --> 01:49:30,207
<i>... as I had not given
a complete explanation.</i>

1462
01:49:30,811 --> 01:49:32,642
<i>Some questions are for answering...</i>

1463
01:49:32,846 --> 01:49:35,644
<i>... others are better left
to torture and torment...</i>

1464
01:49:35,883 --> 01:49:37,145
<i>... for all eternity.</i>

1465
01:49:39,086 --> 01:49:41,077
<i>A nagging itch
for the rest of his life...</i>

1466
01:49:43,957 --> 01:49:46,983
<i>... seemed reasonable, especially since
I did solve his problem.</i>

1467
01:49:47,194 --> 01:49:50,163
<i>He got the tape he'd been waiting for
for so long.</i>

1468
01:49:50,364 --> 01:49:53,060
<i>He wouldn't be throwing anymore
money down the toilet.</i>

1469
01:49:53,267 --> 01:49:56,202
<i>And I gave back his keys.</i>

1470
01:50:04,044 --> 01:50:07,502
<i>This did, in fact, prove to be
my final work experience...</i>

1471
01:50:07,714 --> 01:50:10,114
<i>... with my longtime associate...</i>

1472
01:50:11,785 --> 01:50:14,754
<i>... though I have assured him
that when he someday finds...</i>

1473
01:50:15,022 --> 01:50:16,853
<i>... that he cannot live without me...</i>

1474
01:50:17,057 --> 01:50:19,719
<i>... his position will again
be available to him.</i>

1475
01:50:20,394 --> 01:50:24,728
<i>He thanked me and suggested
that I not hold my breath.</i>

1476
01:50:25,666 --> 01:50:28,328
<i>I also attended the funeral
of the hit man...</i>

1477
01:50:28,568 --> 01:50:31,901
<i>... who died not long after
these events described above.</i>

1478
01:50:32,639 --> 01:50:36,370
<i>For some reason, I felt
a certain kinship with this man...</i>

1479
01:50:36,576 --> 01:50:39,943
<i>... whose life was forever changed
after he failed to remain objective...</i>

1480
01:50:40,147 --> 01:50:42,479
<i>... about the lady blackmailer.</i>

1481
01:50:43,417 --> 01:50:45,977
<i>Which brings me
to the other participant.</i>

1482
01:50:46,653 --> 01:50:49,144
<i>I never made any attempt to find her.</i>

1483
01:50:49,690 --> 01:50:54,627
<i>But if my suspicion is correct, she's
flying through the sky as we speak.</i>

1484
01:50:55,395 --> 01:50:58,125
<i>"...plummeting towards the earth
like a falling bird..."</i>

1485
01:50:58,365 --> 01:51:01,300
<i>... to quote one of my favorite poets.</i>

1486
01:51:01,535 --> 01:51:06,472
<i>After investigating her, I found myself
in better shape than ever before.</i>

1487
01:51:08,208 --> 01:51:12,474
<i>To me, she will always be a singular,
unforgettable event:</i>

1488
01:51:15,248 --> 01:51:18,513
<i>The only time I ever took leave
of my objectivity.</i>

1489
01:51:18,719 --> 01:51:21,847
<i>Perhaps the most able blackmailer
of her time, she was at once...</i>

1490
01:51:22,055 --> 01:51:25,286
<i>... the worthiest opponent
and the greatest ally.</i>

1491
01:51:26,827 --> 01:51:29,819
<i>And the only woman I have ever...</i>

1492
01:51:31,999 --> 01:51:33,296
<i>The only woman.</i>

1493
